1
00:00:03,551 --> 00:00:06,721
(SWORDS CLANGING,
SOLDIERS GRUNTING)

2
00:00:06,821 --> 00:00:08,088
[KARASHIN] WOW! YOU'VE REALLY
GOTTEN

3
00:00:08,189 --> 00:00:09,857
THEIR LEVELS UP, HAVEN'T YOU?
[ISAAC] UH?

4
00:00:09,957 --> 00:00:11,559
[KARASHIN] THEN AGAIN I
SHOULDN'T EXPECT ANYTHING LESS

5
00:00:11,659 --> 00:00:14,762
FROM THE BLACK SWORD KNIGHTS.
YOU'RE A BUNCH OF STUDS!

6
00:00:14,862 --> 00:00:17,665
OF COURSE! THEY KNOW WHO
TO CALL TO GET THINGS DONE!

7
00:00:17,765 --> 00:00:20,034
[ITHERUS] MISTER ISAAC YOU'RE
REALLY AMAZING AT THIS!

8
00:00:20,135 --> 00:00:23,103
YOU JUST KEEP ONE MAKING
ALL OUR SOLDIERS TOUGH.

9
00:00:23,204 --> 00:00:25,540
[ITHERUS] BOTH OF YOU ARE REALLY
HELPING MAIHAMA RIGHT NOW

10
00:00:25,640 --> 00:00:28,108
WITH ALL YOUR HARD
WORK! THANK YOU.

11
00:00:28,209 --> 00:00:30,411
[REZARICK] HAVING YOU SAY THAT
MAKES ALL THE TIME WE'RE

12
00:00:30,511 --> 00:00:32,747
PUTTING IN WORTHWHILE,
MASTER ITHERUS.

13
00:00:32,847 --> 00:00:35,383
WOULDN'T YOU SAY, MISTER ISAAC?
(ISAAC GROWLS)

14
00:00:35,483 --> 00:00:37,051
[KARASHIN] I CAN TELL YOU'VE
BEEN WORKING PRETTY HARD

15
00:00:37,152 --> 00:00:39,254
AT THIS, MISTER ISAAC!
(CHUCKLING)

16
00:00:39,354 --> 00:00:41,989
[ISAAC] (SNARLING) YOU CALL
ME "MISTER" ONE MORE TIME,

17
00:00:42,089 --> 00:00:44,759
AND I'LL CUT YOUR
STUPID HEADS OFF!

18
00:02:17,485 --> 00:02:19,554
[RODERICK] NOW, ABOUT
THIS REQUEST OF YOURS,

19
00:02:19,654 --> 00:02:23,224
TO FACILITATE CONSTRUCTION OF
A LUNAR COMMUNICATION DEVICE.

20
00:02:23,324 --> 00:02:25,160
[SHIROE]
IT'S GONNA COST THIS MUCH?

21
00:02:25,260 --> 00:02:26,961
[RODERICK]
THE PROBLEM'S THE SCALE...

22
00:02:27,061 --> 00:02:28,763
IT'D TAKE MORE THAN THREE
YEARS OF WHAT WE SET ASIDE

23
00:02:28,863 --> 00:02:30,798
FOR THE CITY'S OPERATING BUDGET.

24
00:02:30,898 --> 00:02:32,867
[SHIROE]
YOU HAVE GOT TO BE KIDDING ME.

25
00:02:32,967 --> 00:02:34,602
[RODERICK]
THERE'S ANOTHER CAVEAT.

26
00:02:34,702 --> 00:02:36,937
THERE'S NO GUARANTEE WE CAN MAKE
SOMETHING LIKE THIS WORK

27
00:02:37,037 --> 00:02:39,807
IN THE FIRST PLACE OR KEEP
IT RUNNING AFTER IT'S UP.

28
00:02:39,907 --> 00:02:41,176
[SHIROE]
WELL, OF COURSE.

29
00:02:41,276 --> 00:02:42,977
[RODERICK]
YOU'RE SERIOUS ABOUT THIS?

30
00:02:43,077 --> 00:02:45,480
TRYING TO FIND A
WAY TO GO BACK HOME?

31
00:02:47,315 --> 00:02:50,951
[SHIROE] (EXHALE) I NEVER
THOUGHT IT WOULD BE EASY.

32
00:02:51,051 --> 00:02:52,387
[AKATSUKI] SO WHAT DID YOU TELL
EVERYONE

33
00:02:52,487 --> 00:02:53,821
AT THE ROUND TABLE ANYWAY?

34
00:02:53,921 --> 00:02:55,623
IF WE MAKE CONTACT
WITH THE MOON,

35
00:02:55,723 --> 00:02:57,225
THE TRAVELLERS UP THERE

36
00:02:57,325 --> 00:03:00,261
MIGHT BE ABLE TO GIVE US SOME
IDEA ABOUT HOW TO GET BACK HOME.

37
00:03:00,361 --> 00:03:02,297
THAT BEING SAID, I
DIDN'T GO OUT OF MY WAY

38
00:03:02,397 --> 00:03:05,200
TO RAISE ANYONE'S
EXPECTATIONS, EITHER.

39
00:03:05,666 --> 00:03:07,067
(SIGH)

40
00:03:07,168 --> 00:03:08,303
THE WAY THINGS ARE RIGHT NOW,

41
00:03:08,403 --> 00:03:10,971
THERE'S NO WAY
THEY'D APPROVE IT.

42
00:03:11,071 --> 00:03:11,906
HUH?

43
00:03:12,006 --> 00:03:14,575
UH... WHAT'RE YOU
DOING, AKATSUKI?

44
00:03:14,675 --> 00:03:15,810
[AKATSUKI] REMEMBER
YOUR FOREHEAD.

45
00:03:15,910 --> 00:03:18,112
YOU'RE GETTING OLD
MAN WRINKLES AGAIN.

46
00:03:18,813 --> 00:03:20,548
I FORBID ANY MORE WRINKLES.

47
00:03:21,416 --> 00:03:23,451
I'LL WORK ON IT.

48
00:03:29,590 --> 00:03:33,093
[SERARA] IS WHAT MASTER SHIROE
SAID BEFORE IS ALL TRUE?

49
00:03:33,194 --> 00:03:35,830
I REALLY WOULDN'T MIND
GOING BACK HOME, YOU KNOW?

50
00:03:35,930 --> 00:03:38,133
[MINORI] A LOT OF WHAT HE
SAID IS STILL UNCONFIRMED,

51
00:03:38,233 --> 00:03:40,368
SO WE SHOULD PROBABLY KEEP
IT TO OURSELVES FOR NOW,

52
00:03:40,468 --> 00:03:41,702
SINCE NOTHING'S SET.

53
00:03:41,802 --> 00:03:43,238
[ISUZU] YEAH,
THAT WON'T BE EASY!

54
00:03:43,338 --> 00:03:45,973
THAT'S NOT THE KINDA THING
YOU CAN KEEP SECRET FOR LONG.

55
00:03:46,073 --> 00:03:48,543
SERIOUSLY, JUST THINK ABOUT
WHAT IT REALLY MEANS.

56
00:03:48,643 --> 00:03:51,612
YEAH... IT'S COMPLICATED...

57
00:03:51,712 --> 00:03:56,083
OH MAN, AS MUCH AS I WANT TO
SEE MY MOM AND DAD AGAIN...

58
00:03:56,184 --> 00:03:57,818
I DON'T WANNA LEAVE
ALL THE PEOPLE

59
00:03:57,918 --> 00:04:00,688
WHO'VE BEEN WITH ME
THROUGH THIS WHOLE THING.

60
00:04:00,788 --> 00:04:02,490
THEY'RE IMPORTANT TO ME.

61
00:04:02,590 --> 00:04:03,558
[MINORI]
OH, SERARA...

62
00:04:03,658 --> 00:04:05,493
I HEAR WHAT YOU'RE SAYING.

63
00:04:05,593 --> 00:04:06,694
NOW THAT WE'RE ALL FRIENDS
AND

64
00:04:06,794 --> 00:04:07,995
WE'VE BEEN THROUGH
SO MUCH TOGETHER.

65
00:04:08,095 --> 00:04:09,564
WHAT DO YOU THINK, MINORI?

66
00:04:09,664 --> 00:04:12,200
HUH? WELL, I DON'T KNOW...

67
00:04:12,300 --> 00:04:14,635
I HAVEN'T GIVEN IT
A LOT OF THOUGHT.

68
00:04:15,736 --> 00:04:17,172
MPH?

69
00:04:17,272 --> 00:04:18,773
(EXHALE)

70
00:04:18,873 --> 00:04:20,107
I WOULD IF I COULD.

71
00:04:20,208 --> 00:04:21,476
HUH?

72
00:04:21,576 --> 00:04:23,644
[TOYA] I'M SURE MOST OF US
WOULD DO THE SAME THING...

73
00:04:23,744 --> 00:04:26,981
IT'S NOT LIKE WE WOKE UP ONE DAY
AND SAID WE WANTED TO BE HERE.

74
00:04:27,081 --> 00:04:29,550
[ISUZU] IT'S TRUE. WE'RE
ALL VICTIMS IN THIS.

75
00:04:29,650 --> 00:04:32,353
NONE OF US HAD A CHOICE IN
THE MATTER; THAT'S FOR SURE.

76
00:04:32,453 --> 00:04:34,589
BUT I ALSO WOULDN'T MIND
STAYING HERE EITHER.

77
00:04:34,689 --> 00:04:37,057
I MEAN I FEEL LIKE I'VE
MADE MYSELF USEFUL, Y'KNOW.

78
00:04:37,158 --> 00:04:39,694
IN FACT, I THINK I'VE MANAGED
TO ACCOMPLISH MORE HERE

79
00:04:39,794 --> 00:04:41,962
THAN I EVER DID BACK HOME.

80
00:04:45,099 --> 00:04:46,901
OKAY, TOYA...

81
00:04:48,035 --> 00:04:50,505
[RUDY] I UNDERSTAND WHERE
YOU'RE COMING FROM TOYA.

82
00:04:50,605 --> 00:04:52,240
UH... RUDY...

83
00:04:52,340 --> 00:04:55,476
IT'S NATURAL FOR EVERYONE
TO WANNA GO HOME...

84
00:04:55,576 --> 00:04:59,880
AND SAYING GOODBYE...?
I'M READY FOR THAT.

85
00:04:59,980 --> 00:05:01,549
[RUDY] WHATEVER TOYA WANTS,

86
00:05:01,649 --> 00:05:03,984
AS LONG AS IT ISN'T
ANOTHER FORCED RELOCATION

87
00:05:04,084 --> 00:05:06,754
AT THE HANDS OF SOME
UNFORESEEN CIRCUMSTANCES.

88
00:05:06,854 --> 00:05:08,356
SOUNDS GOOD TO ME.

89
00:05:08,456 --> 00:05:09,657
[ISUZU]
TOYA?

90
00:05:09,757 --> 00:05:11,792
MISS ISUZU, IF YOU END UP
GOING BACK TO YOUR HOMELAND,

91
00:05:11,892 --> 00:05:14,529
WON'T YOU BE ABLE TO PLAY
MUSIC WITH YOUR FATHER?

92
00:05:14,629 --> 00:05:17,665
UH... IT'S NOT THAT SIMPLE...

93
00:05:17,765 --> 00:05:21,469
I DON'T KNOW IF THERE'S A
RIGHT OR WRONG ANSWER RUDY.

94
00:05:23,271 --> 00:05:27,107
[SERARA] OH WHY DOES EVERYTHING
HAVE TO BE SO DIFFICULT?

95
00:05:27,208 --> 00:05:28,209
MPH.

96
00:05:30,010 --> 00:05:32,347
[ISAAC] THE CITY'S GETTIN' MORE
AND MORE LIKE THE OLD AKIHABARA,

97
00:05:32,447 --> 00:05:33,948
ISN'T IT? [MAN] SHORT SLEEVED
T‐SHIRTS HALF OFF TODAY!

98
00:05:34,048 --> 00:05:35,082
[REZARICK] I GUESS OUR
CULTURE'S RUBBING OFF

99
00:05:35,183 --> 00:05:36,317
ON THE PEOPLE OF THE LAND

100
00:05:36,417 --> 00:05:38,052
MORE THAN WE COULD'VE EXPECTED.

101
00:05:38,153 --> 00:05:40,655
[KARASHIN]
IT CERTAINLY HAS.

102
00:05:40,755 --> 00:05:42,157
SO WHAT DO YOU MAKE OF ALL THIS?

103
00:05:42,257 --> 00:05:44,359
[ITHERUS] I LOVE IT!
PEOPLE OF THE LAND NEED

104
00:05:44,459 --> 00:05:47,362
TO EMBRACE ADVENTURER CULTURE
SO WE CAN KEEP GROWING!

105
00:05:47,462 --> 00:05:50,398
MY GRANDFATHER SAYS THAT'S AN
IMPORTANT PART OF OUR FUTURE.

106
00:05:50,498 --> 00:05:53,301
[ISAAC] SPEAKING OF, HOW LONG'RE
YOU GONNA BE FOLLOWING ME?

107
00:05:53,401 --> 00:05:55,536
[ITHERUS] AS LONG AS IT TAKES,
I'VE GOTTA GET TO KNOW

108
00:05:55,636 --> 00:05:57,805
ADVENTURERS LIKE YOU THE SAME
WAY RAYNESHIA DID.

109
00:05:57,905 --> 00:05:59,940
YOU'RE STUCK WITH
ME, MISTER ISAAC!

110
00:06:00,040 --> 00:06:01,776
(ISAAC GROWLING)
[REZARICK] I DON'T SUPPOSE NOW'D

111
00:06:01,876 --> 00:06:03,311
BE A GOOD TIME TO REMIND YOU

112
00:06:03,411 --> 00:06:05,846
THAT PROTECTING THE YOUNG
MASTER'S ONE OF OUR DUTIES.

113
00:06:05,946 --> 00:06:08,249
[ISAAC] HMPH. YEAH,
WHATEVER MAN.

114
00:06:09,384 --> 00:06:11,852
[KARASHIN] THE BOY SEEMS
TO BE AWFULLY FOND OF YOU.

115
00:06:11,952 --> 00:06:13,188
[ISAAC] IT'S NOT MY STYLE.

116
00:06:13,288 --> 00:06:14,922
[KARASHIN] WELL MAYBE
IT SHOULD BE...

117
00:06:15,022 --> 00:06:16,791
A FRIENDSHIP LIKE THIS
CAN MAKE THE TIES BETWEEN

118
00:06:16,891 --> 00:06:18,993
MAIHAMA AND AKIHABARA STRONGER.

119
00:06:19,093 --> 00:06:20,895
IT'S JUST THAT WE'VE GOT
ANOTHER ISSUE WE'RE

120
00:06:20,995 --> 00:06:22,163
GOING TO NEED TO DEAL WITH.

121
00:06:22,263 --> 00:06:24,232
WHAT DO YOU MEAN BY THAT?

122
00:06:24,332 --> 00:06:25,733
[KARASHIN] COME ON. YOU'VE GOTTA
REMEMBER

123
00:06:25,833 --> 00:06:26,967
THE LAST CONFERENCE MEETING.

124
00:06:27,067 --> 00:06:29,370
YOU KNOW, TRYING TO
TALK TO THE MOON?

125
00:06:29,470 --> 00:06:30,938
[ISAAC] YOU MEAN THAT THING THAT
MIGHT TELL US

126
00:06:31,038 --> 00:06:32,507
HOW WE'RE GONNA GET BACK HOME?

127
00:06:32,607 --> 00:06:34,909
[KARASHIN] EXACTLY. AND IT'S
PROBABLY GONNA THROW

128
00:06:35,009 --> 00:06:37,212
A MONKEY WRENCH IN
THIS WORLD'S POLITICS.

129
00:06:37,312 --> 00:06:39,147
COULDN'T CARE LESS ABOUT IT...

130
00:06:39,247 --> 00:06:41,682
ESPECIALLY WHEN POLITICIANS
USE OTHER PEOPLE TO FIGHT.

131
00:06:41,782 --> 00:06:44,819
REALLY? BUT THIS COULD HELP OUR
CHANCES OF GETTING BACK HOME.

132
00:06:44,919 --> 00:06:48,656
I'M MORE OF A SIT AND WAIT KINDA
GUY INSTEAD OF A WORRY‐WART.

133
00:06:48,756 --> 00:06:50,358
YEAH, I GUESS...

134
00:06:50,458 --> 00:06:51,359
COME ON...

135
00:06:51,459 --> 00:06:52,927
A HIGH PRICE TAG DOESN'T MEAN

136
00:06:53,027 --> 00:06:54,729
THAT SWORD'S WORTH A DAMN.
[ITHERUS] HUH?

137
00:06:54,829 --> 00:06:56,764
[ISAAC] REZARICK, YOU
SHOULD KNOW BETTER.

138
00:06:56,864 --> 00:07:00,501
MISTER ISAAC IS MUCH BETTER
JUDGE OF SWORDS THAN I AM.

139
00:07:00,601 --> 00:07:02,470
GIMME A BREAK, WILLYA?

140
00:07:02,570 --> 00:07:04,104
(EXHALE)

141
00:07:06,106 --> 00:07:07,808
HERE... THIS'LL WORK.

142
00:07:08,676 --> 00:07:10,978
AH... OH GOODNESS.

143
00:07:11,078 --> 00:07:13,414
BUT IT'S EXPENSIVE, AND
IT'S LEVEL‐RATING IS

144
00:07:13,514 --> 00:07:16,083
A LOT HIGHER THAN WHAT I
SHOULD BE USING RIGHT NOW.

145
00:07:16,184 --> 00:07:18,586
I CAN'T USE IT YET... LET'S GO.

146
00:07:21,088 --> 00:07:23,224
I WAS TRYING TO
HELP THE KID OUT.

147
00:07:23,324 --> 00:07:25,593
KNOWING HIS OWN LIMITATIONS
IS A GOOD THING.

148
00:07:25,693 --> 00:07:27,995
HE ACTS KINDA LIKE A
KID IN A LOT OF WAYS,

149
00:07:28,095 --> 00:07:29,830
BUT THAT WAS PRETTY IMPRESSIVE.

150
00:07:29,930 --> 00:07:33,534
OKAY... WHATEVER. HUH?

151
00:07:34,034 --> 00:07:35,069
HM?

152
00:07:35,170 --> 00:07:37,438
[REZARICK]
IS SOMETHING... WRONG?

153
00:07:38,306 --> 00:07:41,276
NOTHING... LET'S
GET OUTTA HERE.

154
00:07:43,778 --> 00:07:45,680
[SERJIAD] HOW'S THE TRAINING FOR
THE SOLDIERS

155
00:07:45,780 --> 00:07:47,215
COMING ALONG, MASTER ISAAC?

156
00:07:47,315 --> 00:07:49,184
[ISAAC]
THEY'RE OKAY SO FAR.

157
00:07:49,284 --> 00:07:52,153
THEY'RE LEVELING
UP QUICK ENOUGH.

158
00:07:52,253 --> 00:07:54,021
THAT KIND OF NEWS
IS ENCOURAGING.

159
00:07:54,122 --> 00:07:57,425
TIMES ARE SUCH THAT WE COULD BE
EMBROILED IN WAR AT ANY MOMENT.

160
00:07:57,525 --> 00:07:59,760
DID YOU REALLY HAVE ME COME
OUT HERE TO DRINK TEA

161
00:07:59,860 --> 00:08:02,029
AND MAKE SMALL TALK, OLD MAN?

162
00:08:02,130 --> 00:08:04,965
(CLEARING THROAT)
I'M CONCERNED ABOUT ITHERUS.

163
00:08:05,065 --> 00:08:06,667
[ISAAC]
HUH?

164
00:08:06,767 --> 00:08:09,904
WE'VE DECIDED THAT WE'RE GOING
TO HOLD A GRAND CEREMONY

165
00:08:10,004 --> 00:08:12,440
FOR HIS BIRTHDAY IN A FEW DAYS.

166
00:08:12,540 --> 00:08:15,075
IT WILL ALSO SERVE AS MY
OPPORTUNITY TO NAME HIM

167
00:08:15,176 --> 00:08:17,445
AS THE PROPER HEIR
TO HOUSE COWEN.

168
00:08:17,545 --> 00:08:20,047
THE "PROPER HEIR"?
THAT LITTLE BOY?

169
00:08:20,148 --> 00:08:21,416
[SERJIAD]
HMMM.

170
00:08:21,516 --> 00:08:23,118
I THOUGHT YOU
ALREADY HAD A SON

171
00:08:23,218 --> 00:08:25,520
TO TAKE OVER WHEN YOU
DECIDE TO STEP DOWN.

172
00:08:25,620 --> 00:08:28,088
[SERJIAD]
FERNELLE MARRIED INTO MY FAMILY.

173
00:08:28,189 --> 00:08:30,391
HE'S A MAGNIFICENT
STATESMAN AND WARRIOR,

174
00:08:30,491 --> 00:08:33,294
BUT THE PEOPLE WOULD NEVER
ACCEPT HIS ASCENSION.

175
00:08:33,394 --> 00:08:35,263
THEY WANT MY SUCCESSOR TO HAVE

176
00:08:35,363 --> 00:08:37,932
THE COWEN BLOOD FLOWING
IN THEIR VEINS.

177
00:08:38,032 --> 00:08:39,834
MY DAUGHTER, SARARIYA,
AND FERNELLE

178
00:08:39,934 --> 00:08:42,069
HAVE THREE CHILDREN TOGETHER.

179
00:08:42,170 --> 00:08:44,372
THEIR ELDEST
DAUGHTER, RISSELTHEA,

180
00:08:44,472 --> 00:08:46,307
THEIR SECOND
DAUGHTER, RAYNESHIA,

181
00:08:46,407 --> 00:08:49,109
AND THEIR YOUNGEST OF
COURSE IS ITHERUS.

182
00:08:49,210 --> 00:08:51,812
RISSELTHEA ABANDONED
HER RIGHT AS SUCCESSOR

183
00:08:51,912 --> 00:08:53,948
BY MARRYING OUTSIDE NOBILITY..

184
00:08:54,048 --> 00:08:56,417
LEAVING US WITH
RAYNESHIA AND ITHERUS.

185
00:08:56,517 --> 00:08:58,786
[ISAAC] THAT'S RIGHT, I
FORGOT ABOUT HER, DIDN'T I?

186
00:08:58,886 --> 00:09:02,523
I WAS BLINDED BY WHAT
I THOUGHT WAS RESOLVE.

187
00:09:02,623 --> 00:09:04,792
FRANKLY, HER OUTBURST AT THE
LORDS

188
00:09:04,892 --> 00:09:08,429
WAS A HARSH AWAKENING
AT MY FOOLISH OPTIMISM.

189
00:09:08,529 --> 00:09:11,332
SHE WILL STILL HAVE A ROLE IN
OUR GOVERNMENT,

190
00:09:11,432 --> 00:09:15,503
BUT YOU CAN BE SURE IT
WON'T BE HEAD OF STATE.

191
00:09:15,603 --> 00:09:17,705
SO SHE ISN'T GONNA
BE RUNNING THINGS.

192
00:09:17,805 --> 00:09:18,706
[SERJIAD] AND BESIDES,

193
00:09:18,806 --> 00:09:21,376
A LORDSHIP REQUIRES
A MAN'S QUALITIES.

194
00:09:21,476 --> 00:09:23,778
I'M SURE ITHERUS
WILL GROW INTO THIS.

195
00:09:23,878 --> 00:09:25,813
[ISAAC] SO BASICALLY THIS
WHOLE SUCCESSION THING

196
00:09:25,913 --> 00:09:28,383
HAS BEEN WEIGHING HEAVY
ON YOUR MIND, HUH, CHIEF?

197
00:09:28,483 --> 00:09:31,619
[SERJIAD] (GRUNT) HENCEFORTH,
IT WILL BE ESSENTIAL FOR A LORD

198
00:09:31,719 --> 00:09:34,922
TO FOSTER UNDERSTANDING
WITH THE ADVENTURERS.

199
00:09:35,022 --> 00:09:39,660
MASTER ISAAC, YOU KNOW AS WELL
AS I DO, ITHERUS IS JUST A BOY.

200
00:09:39,760 --> 00:09:43,464
I ASK A FAVOR, PLEASE MENTOR HIM
WHILE YOU'RE HERE.

201
00:09:43,564 --> 00:09:47,335
THEY'RE THINGS YOU KNOW,
WE CANNOT TEACH.

202
00:09:50,205 --> 00:09:51,939
(SIGH)

203
00:09:54,842 --> 00:09:58,078
I REALLY DON'T KNOW ABOUT
ALL THIS, MAN... HM?

204
00:09:58,179 --> 00:09:59,680
(MAID SOBBING)
[ITHERUS] NOW LOOK,

205
00:09:59,780 --> 00:10:02,250
IF THERE'S ANYTHING ELSE YOU
NEED HELP WITH JUST LET ME KNOW.

206
00:10:02,350 --> 00:10:05,186
I'LL TALK TO MY GRANDFATHER
AND SEE WHAT I CAN DO!

207
00:10:05,286 --> 00:10:07,322
[MAID A] THANKS SO
MUCH, YOUNG MASTER!

208
00:10:09,424 --> 00:10:11,859
[ITHERUS] I THOUGHT THAT MAYBE
IF WE WIDENED THIS WATERWAY,

209
00:10:11,959 --> 00:10:13,661
MORE SHIPS COULD PASS THROUGH.

210
00:10:13,761 --> 00:10:15,996
THAT OUGHT TO HELP US
EXPAND OUR MARITIME

211
00:10:16,096 --> 00:10:18,433
TRADE PROFITS MOVING FORWARD.

