00:19:26,914 --> 00:19:28,549
[ISAAC] YOU COWARDS!

432
00:19:28,649 --> 00:19:31,386
[KARASHIN] WOW, ISAAC,
YOU'RE DEFINITELY MY HERO NOW.

433
00:19:31,486 --> 00:19:34,355
[REZARICK] HANG ON A SECOND
YOU COULD USE SOME HEALING.

434
00:19:34,455 --> 00:19:35,723
[ISAAC] I'LL BE OKAY, MAN...

435
00:19:35,823 --> 00:19:37,925
I MADE SURE I DIDN'T GET
A WHOLE LUNG FULL OF IT.

436
00:19:38,025 --> 00:19:40,628
SERIOUSLY, WHY'RE
THESE GUYS SO JACKED?

437
00:19:40,728 --> 00:19:44,365
[KARASHIN] MINAMI WAS SUPPOSEDLY
LEVELING UP PEOPLE OF THE LAND.

438
00:19:44,465 --> 00:19:46,801
I GUESS I OWE YOU BIG TIME
FOR ALL THAT INFORMATION

439
00:19:46,901 --> 00:19:48,903
YOU GAVE ME THE OTHER DAY.

440
00:19:49,003 --> 00:19:50,171
LOOKS LIKE YOUR PRESENT

441
00:19:50,271 --> 00:19:51,972
FROM RODERICK'S MERCHANT
GUILD HELPED.

442
00:19:52,072 --> 00:19:53,741
I STILL HAVEN'T FIGURED
OUT HOW YOU KNEW

443
00:19:53,841 --> 00:19:56,076
WESTELANDE ASSASSINS
WOULD BE COMING?

444
00:19:56,177 --> 00:19:57,945
I THINK I REMEMBER
SAYING INFORMATION

445
00:19:58,045 --> 00:20:00,047
IS A MERCHANT'S BEST FRIEND.

446
00:20:00,915 --> 00:20:02,082
WELL KARASHIN,

447
00:20:02,183 --> 00:20:03,984
YOU'RE NOT AS MUCH OF
A WUSS AS I THOUGHT.

448
00:20:04,084 --> 00:20:06,554
[KARASHIN] YEAH. AND I THOUGHT
YOU WERE ALL BRAWN

449
00:20:06,654 --> 00:20:09,224
AND NO BRAINS.

450
00:20:09,324 --> 00:20:13,261
[ISAAC] ITHERUS, YOU
SHOULD BE SAFE NOW.

451
00:20:13,361 --> 00:20:14,195
[ITHERUS]
UH‐HUH.

452
00:20:14,295 --> 00:20:15,296
DON'T YOU WORRY.

453
00:20:15,396 --> 00:20:17,365
I'M NOT GOIN' ANYWHERE
LITTLE BUDDY 'O MINE!

454
00:20:17,465 --> 00:20:19,434
YOU GOT THAT, SQUIRT....
[ITHERUS] OW...

455
00:20:21,802 --> 00:20:22,603
[ITHERUS]
MM‐HM.

456
00:20:22,703 --> 00:20:23,871
[ISAAC]
HEH...

457
00:20:25,240 --> 00:20:27,942
[ITHERUS] THANK
YOU, MR. ISAAC.

458
00:20:35,183 --> 00:20:38,319
[SHIROE] I SEE. PLEASE LET ME
KNOW IF ANYTHING ELSE HAPPENS.

459
00:20:38,419 --> 00:20:40,721
GOOD WORK, GO AHEAD AND STAY
ON TOP OF THINGS...

460
00:20:40,821 --> 00:20:43,458
THANKS, KARASHIN.
(VOICE CHAT ENDING)

461
00:20:43,558 --> 00:20:44,959
[SHIROE, THINKING]
I KNEW IT.

462
00:20:45,059 --> 00:20:46,861
OUR PRESENCE HERE IS THROWING
ALL THE OTHER SOCIETIES

463
00:20:46,961 --> 00:20:49,464
OUT OF BALANCE.

464
00:20:49,564 --> 00:20:51,532
[SHIROE] WE'VE GOTTA FIND A
WAY TO GET BACK HOME?

465
00:20:51,632 --> 00:20:53,301
(SIGH) (DOOR OPENING)

466
00:20:53,401 --> 00:20:56,704
[REGAN] IT'S BEEN A WHILE,
HASN'T IT, MASTER SHIROE?

467
00:20:56,804 --> 00:21:00,074
[SHIROE] WHY ARE YOU ALWAYS
LURKING AROUND LIKE A CREEP?

468
00:21:01,108 --> 00:21:02,677
[REGAN] I FINALLY
MADE SOME HEADWAY

469
00:21:02,777 --> 00:21:04,345
IN MY INVESTIGATION OF SUSUKINO.

470
00:21:04,445 --> 00:21:06,447
I DO APOLOGIZE FOR
IT TAKING SO LONG.

471
00:21:06,547 --> 00:21:08,749
[REGAN] WOULD YOU LIKE
TO HEAR ABOUT IT?

472
00:21:08,849 --> 00:21:10,218
[SHIROE] HOW'S
EVERYONE DOING THERE?

473
00:21:10,318 --> 00:21:11,686
[REGAN] THEY'RE DOING
WELL, AND THEY MADE SURE

474
00:21:11,786 --> 00:21:13,754
TO TELL ME TO SEND
YOU THEIR REGARDS.

475
00:21:13,854 --> 00:21:15,190
[SHIROE] AND I SUPPOSE
THE SITUATION

476
00:21:15,290 --> 00:21:16,991
WITH THE TRANSPORT
GATES IS THE SAME?

477
00:21:17,091 --> 00:21:19,660
[REGAN] YES. AS I CONTINUED MY
RESEARCH,

478
00:21:19,760 --> 00:21:20,995
I DISCOVERED THAT FAIRY RINGS

479
00:21:21,095 --> 00:21:23,931
ARE INDEED AFFECTED
BY THE LUNAR CYCLES.

480
00:21:24,031 --> 00:21:26,367
WHICH MAKES THE LEGEND OF
ANCIENT ALV RUINS

481
00:21:26,467 --> 00:21:28,969
UP ON THE MOON ALL THE MORE
INTERESTING. (CHUCKLING)

482
00:21:29,069 --> 00:21:30,671
[SHIROE, THINKING] THERE
MIGHT ACTUALLY BE A CONTROL

483
00:21:30,771 --> 00:21:34,041
BEACON ON THE MOON AFFECTING
THE TRANSPORT COORDINATES.

484
00:21:34,142 --> 00:21:36,411
THE MOON'S DEFINITELY IT...

485
00:21:37,478 --> 00:21:39,214
[SHIROE] WE'VE GOTTA FIND
A WAY TO TALK TO THEM.

486
00:21:39,314 --> 00:21:40,548
[REGAN]
"TALK TO THEM"?

487
00:21:40,648 --> 00:21:41,816
[SHIROE]
YEAH.

488
00:21:41,916 --> 00:21:43,251
RIGHT NOW, WE'RE INVESTIGATING

489
00:21:43,351 --> 00:21:45,953
ANYTHING THAT MIGHT SEND
THE ADVENTURERS HOME.

490
00:21:46,053 --> 00:21:47,855
AND AT THE MOMENT, COMMUNICATION
WITH THE MOON SEEMS

491
00:21:47,955 --> 00:21:49,424
TO BE OUR BEST OPTION.

492
00:21:49,524 --> 00:21:50,791
[REGAN]
AH. (MUNCHES)

493
00:21:50,891 --> 00:21:52,327
[SHIROE] HOWEVER, THE
COST OF THE EQUIPMENT

494
00:21:52,427 --> 00:21:54,129
TO DO IT HAS PROVEN
PROHIBITIVE.

495
00:21:54,229 --> 00:21:55,563
[SHIROE] SO THINGS
AREN'T VERY PROMISING.

496
00:21:55,663 --> 00:21:58,566
[REGAN] MASTER SHIROE,
SHIBUYA HAS AN ANTENNA.

497
00:21:58,666 --> 00:21:59,967
[SHIROE]
I KNOW.

498
00:22:00,067 --> 00:22:02,203
[SHIROE] SHIBUYA'S OLD
RADIO AND TV COMPLEX.

499
00:22:02,303 --> 00:22:04,605
YAMATO'S ONLY
COMMUNICATIONS FACILITY.

500
00:22:04,705 --> 00:22:08,909
WE LOOKED INTO IT A WHILE BACK,
AND I DON'T REMEMBER IT WORKING.

501
00:22:09,009 --> 00:22:11,846
I DUNNO WHEN I INVESTIGATED IT,
I GOT A SIGNAL,

502
00:22:11,946 --> 00:22:13,481
FAINT, BUT THERE NONETHELESS.

503
00:22:13,581 --> 00:22:15,850
PERHAPS THERE MIGHT
STILL BE A CHANCE?

504
00:22:15,950 --> 00:22:17,585
YOU GOT A SIGNAL?

505
00:22:17,685 --> 00:22:18,919
(VOICE CHAT PING)
UH...?

506
00:22:19,019 --> 00:22:20,221
[ISAAC, VOICE CHAT]
HEY, VILLAIN IN GLASSES!

507
00:22:20,321 --> 00:22:21,822
YOU KNOW WHAT'S GOING ON?!

508
00:22:21,922 --> 00:22:23,891
NPCS'RE DROPPING LIKE FLIES!

509
00:22:23,991 --> 00:22:25,326
WHAT THE HELL IS THIS?!

510
00:22:25,426 --> 00:22:27,462
WHAT WAS THAT?! WHAT
ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?!

511
00:22:27,562 --> 00:22:28,463
JUST SLOW DOWN...!

512
00:22:28,563 --> 00:22:29,697
[MINORI] MASTER SHIROE!
[BOTH] UH...!

513
00:22:29,797 --> 00:22:30,698
WE NEED HELP!

514
00:22:30,798 --> 00:22:31,966
WE'VE GOT A PROBLEM!

515
00:22:32,066 --> 00:22:33,968
[ALL]
HUH?!

516
00:24:15,736 --> 00:24:17,638
[AKATSUKI, VOICEOVER] THE PEOPLE
BEGIN MYSTERIOUSLY FALLING

517
00:24:17,738 --> 00:24:18,939
INTO A DEEP SLEEP...

518
00:24:19,039 --> 00:24:22,177
AS A BLACK SHADOW
ECLIPSES THE MOONLIT SKY.

519
00:24:22,277 --> 00:24:26,314
SHIBUYA BECOMES A RAID ZONE,
AND IS OVERRUN BY MONSTERS.

520
00:24:26,414 --> 00:24:28,316
WHO COULD BE TRYING TO STOP THE
ADVENTURERS

521
00:24:28,416 --> 00:24:30,651
FROM RETURNING TO THE
WORLD THEY CAME FROM?

522
00:24:30,751 --> 00:24:32,287
SHIROE DIVES INTO COMBAT,

523
00:24:32,387 --> 00:24:34,355
CONCEALING THE UNCERTAINTY
WITHIN HIS HEART.

524
00:24:34,455 --> 00:24:37,492
[SHIROE] MY COMRADES
ARE ALWAYS BESIDE ME.

